content.text:
I'll help you warm up by exploring the current directory structure and understanding what we're working with.

<tool_code>
Bash
command: pwd && ls -la
description: Show current working directory and list contents
</tool_code>

<tool_code>
Bash
command: find . -type f -name "*.py" | head -10
description: Find Python files in current directory and subdirectories
</tool_code>

<tool_code>
Bash
command: find . -type f -name "*.js" | head -10
description: Find JavaScript files in current directory and subdirectories
</tool_code>

<tool_code>
Bash
command: find . -type f -name "*.md" | head -10
description: Find Markdown files in current directory and subdirectories
</tool_code>
